value.title: Kamala Harris: Cancel Student Loan Debt And Make College Tuition-Free
value.excerpt: Harris (D-CA), the Democratic nominee for vice president, said that a Biden-Harris administration would cancel student loan debt for some students at Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HCBU’s).

value.title: Campaign adviser argues Trump 'well positioned' to flip blue states, despite polling
value.excerpt: Less than two months away from a presidential election that most experts predict will be determined by President Donald Trump's ability to defend the 2016 electoral map, one of Trump's top advisers argued Sunday that the campaign is actually poised to go on the offensive.

value.title: The Point: Trump's coronavirus problem isn't getting better
value.excerpt: With just 51 days until the 2020 election, it will be here before you know it. Every Sunday, I deliver to your inbox the 5 BIG storylines you need to know to understand the upcoming week on the campaign trail. And they're ranked -- so the No. 1 story is the most important of the coming week.

value.title: Bloomberg plans to spend at least $100 million in Florida to support Biden
value.excerpt: Billionaire and former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg is planning to spend at least $100 million in the crucial battleground of Florida in support of Democratic nominee Joe Biden, a source familiar with the plans confirmed to CNN.

value.title: Airport: Trump rally would break 50-person limit; president says he's coming to Nevada
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump may have to find a new home for planned weekend campaign rallies in Reno and Las Vegas after local officials warned the events would violate Nevada’s ban on gatherings of more than 50 people during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: EXCLUSIVE-Russian state hackers suspected in targeting Biden campaign firm – sources
value.excerpt: Microsoft Corp recently alerted one of Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden’s main election campaign advisory firms that it had been targeted by suspected Russian state-backed hackers, according to three people briefed on the matter.

value.title: The DOJ's Move to Take Over Trump's Law Suit May Be Legal. But Is It Appropriate?
value.excerpt: The Justice Department moved to take over President Donald Trump’s defense against a woman who claims he defamed her when he denied her accusation that he sexually assaulted her.

value.title: Peter Strzok: "I Continue To Believe That Donald Trump Is Compromised By The Russians"

value.title: Strzok: 'I continue to believe that Donald Trump is compromised by the Russians'
value.excerpt: Former FBI agent Peter Strzok told NBC’s Chuck Todd Sunday that he still believes President Trump to be “compromised by the Russians.”

value.title: Biden campaign adviser defends March rallies, denies Dem opposed travel restrictions
value.excerpt: Biden campaign senior policy adviser Jake Sullivan accused President Trump of failing to properly address the coronavirus pandemic in its early stages, while defending the Democratic presidential nominee's decision to hold rallies after the CDC advised against it.

value.title: President Donald Trump says Big Ten football might happen without Michigan, Michigan State
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump believes Big Ten is getting closer to a return to football, but says Michigan and Michigan State might not be part of it.

value.title: Mike Bloomberg to spend at least $100 million in Florida to benefit Joe Biden
value.excerpt: The promised spending, mainly on advertising, will go to encouraging early voting in a state central to Donald Trump’s reelection hopes.

value.title: Analysis: Why Biden's national lead matters
value.excerpt: Poll of the week: A new Monmouth University poll finds that former Vice President Joe Biden holds a 51% to 44% lead over President Donald Trump among likely voters. Among registered voters, it's Biden 51% to 42% for Trump.

value.title: Fact check: Trump says his coronavirus deception was Churchillian. Scholars of Churchill say he's wrong
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump argued Thursday that his decision to mislead Americans about the severity of the coronavirus threat wasn't just the right thing to do -- it was positively Churchillian.

value.title: Peter Strzok: Russians have 'leverage over' Donald Trump

value.title: Bloomberg to back Biden by spending $100M in Florida
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's onetime rival, billionaire Mike Bloomberg, will spend $100 million to get Biden elected in Florida.

value.title: Federal workers will soon see Trump bump in pay -- but there's a catch
value.excerpt: Many federal workers will soon see a few hundred dollars more in their paychecks, thanks to a coronavirus relief measure signed last month by President Donald Trump.

value.title: Donald Trump says he didn't want to panic people ... then he tweeted this?

value.excerpt: Forty-six years ago this month, President Gerald Ford made one of the most controversial announcements in American political history: He pardoned Richard Nixon.
